      },
      "lineNbr": 229,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T14:34:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "not for this CL, but I wonder if using \u003ctable\u003e would be simpler for console. Because we are rendering a table and need heights and widths to be synchronized, so it looks like a grid.\n\nif not table, I suspect using `display: grid` might be simpler.",
      "revId": "ea0f71d863ef67c20e85670127b1b793221abb34",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "40097fae_8f51dd6b",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/appengine/templates/pages/console.html",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 229,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T22:52:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "anecdotally, tables (and probably grids) take a lot longer to render than flexboxes because for flexboxes, the layout engine only needs to consider sizing in one dimension.  But for tables, if a single cell changes, it triggers a whole bunch of re-layout to get things to be the right sizes in both the x and y dimensions.  This is particularly problematic when the timestamp code activates and we have a 200 commit console (layout time goes through the roof)\n\nso despite this looking like a hack, the fact that we specify the size manually means that it\u0027s one less thing for the layout engine to have to figure out by itself.",
      "parentUuid": "54fabdaf_faced3ad",
      "revId": "ea0f71d863ef67c20e85670127b1b793221abb34",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
