        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T22:52:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We can\u0027t compute the height until the descriptions are visible, and they default to display: none on load.  If they are visible on load, that turns into a lot of visual jank.\n\nMeasuring the performance impact of expanding, it is 150ms of scripting and 458ms of rendering.  If we save the height computation each time, that saves 25% of the time, but adds a bit of complexity.  I figured this was fast enough it wasn\u0027t worth the time.",
      "parentUuid": "8530a670_e91aff17",
      "revId": "ea0f71d863ef67c20e85670127b1b793221abb34",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
